main event: A dull gray object was observed for 10-15 seconds passing to the left of Regulus and to the right of Uranus on April 10, 1964.
interesting points: The sighting duration was relatively brief, lasting only 10-15 seconds., The object was described as dull gray in color., The sighting took place between the stars Regulus and Uranus., No moonlight was present during the observation., The report was forwarded from AFICAD by Lt Colonel Charles Suson.
